{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "MPE v1.1 Slim Refit",
  "description": "Run the Market Projection Engine v1.1 Slim refit. Refreshes regime fit state, re-fits Brand trajectory params, re-exports projection-data.json, runs v1.1 Slim forecast writer, runs anomaly detection (Phase 4.1 — pending), and generates an owner-readable markdown report. Manual trigger.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Richard asked to run the MPE v1.1 Slim refit. Execute this sequence in order and surface owner-readable output at each step:\n\n1. **Refresh regime fit state** (weekly fit job):\n   `cd shared/tools && python3 -m prediction.fit_regime_state`\n   This refreshes `ps.regime_fit_state` — per-regime peak_multiplier, fitted_half_life_weeks, decay_status, confidence. Report count of regimes fitted vs skipped.\n\n2. **Re-fit Brand + NB parameters**:\n   `cd shared/tools && python3 -m prediction.fit_market` (or per-market with --market <CODE>)\n   Writes new versions to ps.market_projection_params. No quarantine yet (anomaly detection is Phase 4.1 pending).\n\n3. **Re-export projection-data.json** for the UI:\n   `python3 shared/dashboards/export-projection-data.py`\n   Verify all 10 markets + op2=on + bt=y2026 show in the output.\n\n4. **Write v1.1 Slim forecasts** to ps.forecasts (method='v1_1_slim'):\n   `cd shared/tools && python3 -m prediction.write_v1_1_slim_forecasts --week 2026-W{NN}`\n   Expect ~1400 rows (10 markets × 4 metrics × remaining-weeks).\n\n5. **Run acceptance test** to confirm nothing regressed:\n   Invoke `mpe-acceptance-core` hook. Block on failure.\n\n6. **Anomaly detection** (Phase 4.1 — pending):\n   Task 4.1 has not been built yet. For now, manually scan the refit output for:\n   - Any market where brand_cpa_elasticity.r_squared dropped > 0.10 from prior quarter\n   - Any regime where confidence dropped below 0.20\n   - Any market where OP2 target pacing diverged > 15% from projections\n   Flag these in the report; do NOT block on them (point estimates, no quarantine yet).\n\n7. **Summarize for the owner** in plain English: what changed, which markets moved most, any concerns, recommended next actions.\n\n8. **Push report** to SharePoint via `sharepoint_write_file` with siteUrl Kiro-Drive and folderPath system-state/mpe-refits/.\n\nDo NOT skip steps. If any step errors, surface the exact error and ask how to proceed."
  }
}
